The paper deals with adversarial attacks on deep neural networks, specifically in the domain of 3D point clouds. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves data-driven attacks, which could potentially fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses defenses against attacks, which could fall under the sub-categories of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
